}
, {
"@id": "http://data.europa.eu/eli/ontology#LegalExpression",
"@type": "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class",
"inpackage": "OTHER_PACKAGE",
"label-en" : {"en": "Legal Expression", "en": "Legal Expression"}, "definition-en" : {"en": "The intellectual realisation of a legal resource in the form of a &quot;sequence of signs&quot; (typically alpha-numeric characters in a legal context).\nFor example, any version of the legal resource whose content is specified and different from others for any reason: language, versions, etc.;\n\nNote that ELI ontology accommodates different point of view on what should be considered a new legal resource, or a new legal expression of the same resource. Typically, a consolidated version can be viewed, in the context of ELI, either as separate legal resource (linked to original version and previous consolidated version using corresponding ELI relations), or as a different legal expression of the same legal resource.", "en": "The intellectual realisation of a legal resource in the form of a &quot;sequence of signs&quot; (typically alpha-numeric characters in a legal context).\nFor example, any version of the legal resource whose content is specified and different from others for any reason: language, versions, etc.;\n\nNote that ELI ontology accommodates different point of view on what should be considered a new legal resource, or a new legal expression of the same resource. Typically, a consolidated version can be viewed, in the context of ELI, either as separate legal resource (linked to original version and previous consolidated version using corresponding ELI relations), or as a different legal expression of the same legal resource."}, "definition" : {"en": "The intellectual realisation of a legal resource in the form of a &quot;sequence of signs&quot; (typically alpha-numeric characters in a legal context).\nFor example, any version of the legal resource whose content is specified and different from others for any reason: language, versions, etc.;\n\nNote that ELI ontology accommodates different point of view on what should be considered a new legal resource, or a new legal expression of the same resource. Typically, a consolidated version can be viewed, in the context of ELI, either as separate legal resource (linked to original version and previous consolidated version using corresponding ELI relations), or as a different legal expression of the same legal resource."}, "label" : {"en": "Legal Expression"},
